                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(2)\">On the Lying Prophets.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Therefore thus says the Lord God; because</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">you have spoken vanity, and seen lies,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">therefore, behold, I am against you, says</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">the Lord God, and my hand shall be upon</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">the prophets that see vanity, and that</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">divine lies; they shall not be in the</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">assembly of my people, neither shall</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">they be written in the writing of the</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">house of <placeName>Israel</placeName>, neither\n                                        shall they</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">enter into the land of\n                                                  <placeName>Israel</placeName>, and</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Joy shall know that I am thy Lord</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">God.    Ezekiel XIII. 889.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Various are the ways practiced by seducers<lb/> of\n                                        all times, and chiefly by such who proposed<lb/> themselves\n                                        to seduce the people of God; the most<lb/> dangerous,\n                                        however, were such as begun with their<lb/> preaching, of a\n                                        pretended improving of hearts and<lb/> reason of mankind;\n                                        disguising as much as possible,<lb/> their irreligious\n                                        conduct, and the real feelings<lb/> of their depraved\n                                        heart.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I. O. begun <sic>likwise</sic> with his sermon on\n                                        the<lb/> mount, saying: Thank not that I am come to\n                                        destroy<lb/> the</p>"
                  },
