                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the laws or the prophets. I am not come to destroy<lb/> but to\n                                                  <sic>fulfil</sic>; for verily, I say unto you,\n                                        till heaven<lb/> and earth past one jot or one little shall\n                                        in no wise<lb/> past from the law till all be fulfilled.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">He and her disciples ended with the abolition<lb/>\n                                        of nearly all, the precepts taught by\n                                                  <persName>Moses</persName> and<lb/> the\n                                        prophets.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">However, our readers could be induced to\n                                        believe,<lb/> that for <hi rend=\"underline\">a member of the\n                                                  Jewish religious society</hi><lb/> it might be <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">his mission to strive\n                                                  earnestly</hi><lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">to render his religion that of the\n                                                  world</hi>; not<lb/> at all, God has given 613\n                                        commandments only<lb/> to the Israelites, for other nations\n                                        Seven<lb/> commandments; and from there was already<lb/>\n                                        revealed six to <persName>Adam</persName> and after that\n                                        time<lb/> re<add>?</add> to <persName>Noah</persName> with\n                                        the addition of <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><add>?</add> Talmud\n                                        Sanhevrin<add>?</add><lb/> folio 56. and Tad <add>?</add>\n                                                  Hilchat<add>?</add> Melachim.</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add>\n                              </p>"
