                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>And if we observe attentively the course of events we<lb/> see a\n                                                  <sic>graduel</sic> progress in the amelioration of\n                                        the religious<lb/> state of the Christians and\n                                                  <sic>principaly</sic> under<add>?</add> the<lb/>\n                                        Protestant sects who by the reading of our holy songs,<lb/>\n                                        here learn to revere the God of\n                                                  <placeName>Israel</placeName> as the Lord<lb/> of\n                                        all mankind; undoubtful we may apply on<lb/> thousands of\n                                        them the sentence of the Talmud<lb/> (<add>Hebrew</add>)\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You see by this that the observation of the\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> is sufficient for other nations<lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> And if God has chosen us as the\n                                                  <sic>ofspring</sic> of his<lb/> beloved servants\n                                                  <add>Hebrew</add> to be a priestly<lb/> kingdom\n                                        and a holy people, it is by no means our sake<lb/> to strive\n                                        to render our religion that of the word; in the<lb/>\n                                        contrary, we begin always with making official<lb/>ties when\n                                        somebody of other nations would present him<lb/>self to\n                                        accept our precepts and laws (Tez Talmad Taba<lb/>moth folio 47.)<lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>"
                  },
