                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><add>Hebrew</add><lb/> and ibidem <add>Hebrew</add></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If any body would in the contrary ascertain that\n                                        it<lb/> might be our duty to make prosylites, he would show\n                                        never<lb/> to have understood <add>Hebrew</add> or that he\n                                        is<lb/> a deceiver and willing to seduce us; and every\n                                        Israelite of<lb/> sound religious principles will agree that\n                                        in con<lb/>cordance of the cited places the intention of the\n                                        Talmud<lb/> (Perachim folio 80) <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add></p>\n                              <p>is only that by the exile<add>?</add> of our nation the\n                                        gentiles<lb/> being somewhat acquainted with our\n                                        scriptures<lb/> will find back in them this a long time ago\n                                        for<lb/> their lost covenant that God with\n                                                  <persName>Noah</persName> and his Gene<lb/>rations\n                                        and that by the word <add>Hebrew</add> here must<lb/> be\n                                        understood <add>Hebrew</add></p>\n                              <p>And if there be some other hidden meaning in it: <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add> surely it will never<lb/> be like the\n                                        absurd idea of false prophets of our times,<lb/> that we\n                                        should reform our system in order to make <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">by it</hi> the<lb/> unity of God\n                                        the basis of the faith of mankind.</p>\n                              <p><add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>Hebrew</add>!</p>"
